An elementary sampling circuit is composed of a switch and a capacitor [as seen in Fig. 13.9(a)]. A metal-oxide-semiconductor field-effect transistor (MOSFET) can act as a switch [refer to Fig. 13.9(b)], as it can remain in an 'on' state while carrying zero current.

