How can we ensure that the charge injected by $M_{1}, \Delta q_{1}$, equals that absorbed by $M_{2}, \Delta q_{2}$? Assume that half of $M_{1}$'s channel charge is injected onto $C_{H}$, i.e.,

$$
\begin{equation*}
