\end{equation*}
$$

Given that $\Delta q_{2}=W_{2} L_{2} C_{o x}\left(V_{C K}-V_{i n}-V_{T H 2}\right)$, if we select $W_{2}=0.5 W_{1}$ and $L_{2}=L_{1}$, then $\Delta q_{2}=\Delta q_{1}$. However, the assumption of equal charge distribution between source and drain is generally inaccurate, making this method less appealing.

